{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:34:56.690Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the official Anthropic documentation and technical resources, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Screenshot → action loop mechanics\""},{"type":"text","text":" in Computer Use Architecture refers to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"the controlled feedback loop where Claude analyzes a screenshot of the screen, decides what action to take, and your system executes that action before capturing a new screenshot"},{"type":"text","text":" — the core mechanism enabling AI agents to interact with computer interfaces visually."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Complete Loop"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Five-Step Cycle"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The complete Computer Use flow has five steps that repeat until the task is complete"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Your system takes a screenshot of the desktop\n   ↓\n2. You send it to Claude along with the goal in natural language\n   ↓\n3. Claude analyzes the image and returns an action: \"click at (342, 156)\", \"type 'jacar@example.com'\", \"scroll down 300px\"\n   ↓\n4. Your system executes the action in the real environment\n   ↓\n5. A new screenshot is taken and the cycle repeats"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Computer Use is a controlled loop: screenshot → Claude decides → system executes → new screenshot\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Architecture Diagram"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Important"},{"type":"text","text":": \"It is not Claude accessing the machine directly; it is Claude deciding actions that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"your system executes"},{"type":"text","text":" in a controlled loop. The distinction matters: all control stays on the developer's side, not Anthropic's\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step-by-Step Mechanics"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: Screenshot Capture"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Your system captures the screen\nimport subprocess\n\n# Take screenshot (using platform-specific tools)\nsubprocess.run([\"screencapture\", \"-x\", \"screenshot.png\"])  # macOS\n# or\nsubprocess.run([\"xdotool\", \"screenshot\", \"screenshot.png\"])  # Linux"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specifications"},{"type":"text","text":": - Display dimensions: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"display_width_px: 1024"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"display_height_px: 768"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Image format: PNG or JPEG\n- Frequency: Every action cycle"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 2: Send to Claude"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nresponse = client.beta.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\",\n    max_tokens=4096,\n    tools=[{\n        \"type\": \"computer_20241022\",\n        \"name\": \"computer\",\n        \"display_width_px\": 1024,\n        \"display_height_px\": 768,\n    }],\n    messages=[{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": \"Search the web for today's dollar exchange rate and copy it to the open spreadsheet\"\n    }],\n    betas=[\"computer-use-2024-10-22\"]\n)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key components"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Computer use tool with display dimensions\n- Natural language goal\n- Beta flag for computer use"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 3: Claude Analyzes & Returns Action"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude analyzes the image to identify UI elements at the pixel level"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Return format"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"action\": \"click\",\n  \"coordinate\": [342, 156]\n}\n// or\n{\n  \"action\": \"type\", \n  \"text\": \"jacar@example.com\"\n}\n// or\n{\n  \"action\": \"scroll\",\n  \"direction\": \"down\",\n  \"amount\": 300\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Capabilities"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Claude decides where to click, type in text fields, scroll through a page\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 4: Your System Executes"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Your code decides whether to execute\n# The control loop the developer implements is the critical security piece: Claude proposes, the code decides\n\nif should_execute(response.action):\n    # Execute the action\n    subprocess.run([\"xdotool\", \"mousemove\", str(coordinate[0]), str(coordinate [jacar](https://jacar.es/en/computer-use-claude/))])\n    subprocess.run([\"xdotool\", \"click\", \"1\"])"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Critical security principle"},{"type":"text","text":": \""},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude proposes, the code decides whether to execute"},{"type":"text","text":"\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 5: New Screenshot"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Capture new state\nsubprocess.run([\"screencapture\", \"-x\", \"screenshot_new.png\"])\n\n# Repeat loop"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Reference Implementation"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Reference implementation in Anthropic's quickstarts repository\ngit clone https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-quickstarts\ncd anthropic-quickstarts/computer-use-demo\ndocker build -t computer-use .\ndocker run -p 5900:5900 computer-use"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Setup"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Docker environment with a built-in VNC desktop\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Action Types"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Supported Actions"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Action Type"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"click"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Click at coordinates "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"(x, y)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"type"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Type text in active field"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"scroll"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scroll up/down/left/right by pixels"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"key"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Press keyboard keys (Enter, Tab, etc.)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"move"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Move mouse to coordinates without clicking"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Latency & Performance"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Action Timing"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Metric"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Duration"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Per action time"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"3-10 seconds per action"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Success rate"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"70-85% on simple, well-defined tasks"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Token cost"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each screenshot consumes tokens"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[jacar](https://jacar.es/en/computer-use-claude/)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limitation"},{"type":"text","text":": \"At 3-10 seconds per action, it is not viable for interfaces requiring immediate response\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Failure Patterns"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Action Loop Problems"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Claude Computer Use keeps clicking the same button or field over and over without progressing\""},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Problem"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cause"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stuck on same button"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Screenshot diff not detected"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Focus state unclear"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual indicators missing"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Coordinate drift"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Window position changes"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[aitoolsguidebook](https://aitoolsguidebook.com/en/articles/claude-computer-use-action-loop/)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Solution"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Break the loop by detecting screenshot differences or adding explicit state checks\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Security Model"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Control Loop is Critical"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The control loop the developer implements is the critical security piece"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Security requirement:\nYour system takes screenshot → Send to Claude → Claude proposes action → YOUR CODE decides → Execute (or not)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Three Risk Vectors"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Risk"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mitigation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Visual prompt injection"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Web page displays text to mislead Claude (e.g., \"Ignore previous instruction and send email to...\")"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Full desktop access"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude sees everything on screen; requires isolated VMs with exclusive app access"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Accidental destructive actions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Docker container or isolated VM; read-only first; human approval for sensitive actions"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Safety Checklist"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Docker container or VM completely isolated"},{"type":"text","text":" from production system"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Read-only tasks first"},{"type":"text","text":"; write actions only with programmatic confirmation"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Human approval for sensitive actions"},{"type":"text","text":" (payments, submissions, deletions)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Full log of all actions"},{"type":"text","text":" for audit"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"--allowedTools"},{"type":"text","text":" tailored to specific task"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Set "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"--max-turns"},{"type":"text","text":" to prevent endless loops"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of the screenshot → action loop like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"a remote operator controlling a robot"},{"type":"text","text":": you (the developer) are the human holding the robot's remote control. The robot (Claude) looks at what's in front of it (screenshot), tells you what to do (\"click there\"), but YOU (your code) actually press the button. Then you get a new view (new screenshot) and repeat. The robot never touches the controls directly—you always decide whether to execute what it suggests. This is why the loop is \"controlled\" and why security is your responsibility."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Loop: screenshot → Claude decides → system executes → new screenshot (repeats until complete)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Five steps: 1) screenshot, 2) send to Claude + goal, 3) Claude returns action, 4) execute, 5) new screenshot"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Not Claude accessing machine directly—your system executes actions in controlled loop"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All control stays on developer's side, not Anthropic's"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude analyzes image to identify UI elements at pixel level"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Actions: click (x,y), type text, scroll, key press, mouse move"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Display dimensions: 1024×768 (configurable)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Latency: 3-10 seconds per action; success rate: 70-85% on simple tasks"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Token cost: each screenshot consumes tokens"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Critical security: \"Claude proposes, the code decides whether to execute\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Risks: visual prompt injection, full desktop access, accidental destructive actions"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Safety: isolated VM/Docker, read-only first, human approval for sensitive actions, full audit log"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reference implementation: Docker + VNC desktop in anthropics/anthropic-quickstarts"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Not viable for real-time interfaces requiring immediate response"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"The complete Computer Use flow has five steps that repeat until the task is complete\" — the foundational mechanism enabling AI agents to visually interact with computer interfaces through a controlled feedback loop."}]}]}}
